      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You absolutely should rest, ice, and elevate your ankle immediately to stop the swelling from getting worse. Do not try to \"see if it gets better\" because your body is screaming for help right now, and waiting is the fastest way to turn a sprain into a chronic injury.\nTake a painkiller like ibuprofen if you can afford it, and apply a cold pack wrapped in a towel for 15 minutes at a time. If you feel any numbness or tingling in your toes, stop immediately and call 911, because that is a sign of nerve damage that requires surgery, not a home remedy.",
